message.content:
cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper is about developing tools for manual annotation of multimedia content, specifically audio, which is relevant to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Sound (cs.SD), Multimedia (cs.MM), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on the annotation of audio content, cs.SD and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of taxonomies, which is relevant to cs.IR and cs.CL. Finally, the user-centered development approach and evaluation of the tools falls under cs.HC.
